HEADWORD: Rosacic
<hw>Ro*sac"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Rosaceous</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Old med. Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining
to, or designating, an acid (called also <xex>lithic acid</xex>) found
in certain red precipitates of urine. See <er>Uric</er>.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
